&TUTORIAL -------------- PAN EDIT - EDIT OPTION ----------------------- TUTORIAL
&NEXT SELECTION ===>%SELECT                             &
&
&                    &-----------------------------------&
&                    &-            PAN EDIT             -&
&                    &-        OPTION ' ' - EDIT        -&
&                    &-----------------------------------$
$
$ THE EDIT FUNCTION PERFORMS THE FOLLOWING FUNCTIONS:
$   1. IF PAN MEMBER IS NOT CURRENTLY 'OWNED' BY A TSO USER,  IT IS
$      RETRIEVED INTO THE SPF DATASET SPECIFIED.  IF 'OWNED' BY THE TSO
$      USER ENTERING THE EDIT OPTION,  SPF EDIT IS CALLED WITHOUT A
$      RETRIEVE.  IF THE MEMBER IS OWNED BY ANOTHER TSO USER, THE EDIT
$      REQUEST IS DENIED;  THE MEMBER CANNOT BE RETRIEVED.
$
$   2. IF THE MEMBER IS COBOL OR ASSEMBLER,  AND IT IS NOT 'NOFORMAT',
$      THE SAME 'AUDIT TRAIL' CONSTANTS ARE INSERTED AS IN BATCH
$      PROCCESSING;  THE MODULE IS RESEQUENCED USING STANDARD SPF OR
$      COBOL SEQUENCE NUMBERS.
$
                           (CONTINUED ON NEXT PAGE)
<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8) LIST(' ') RETURN(' ');
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTPANE  ');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTPANE2 ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTPANE11');
<END>
